issue.title: Roles / Contracts
issue.body:
ISP
 - mints tokens for various package-offerings of internet 
 - put them on a marketplace

Donor (Wyre + Fortmatic)
 - buys internet tokens on marketplace
 - transfers them to a charity (do these two happen in one transaction) 

Charity
 - decides who gets what internet packages that donors have donated

Consumer (Fortmatic)
 - gets a token from the charity for an internet package
 - trades it back to the ISP for service

Design and Implement the  `InternetFaucetFund` Smart Contract
issue.body:
# Internet Faucet Fund Smart Contract

The Donation contract will:

*  receive payments from those donating
*  redeem the internet tokens
* allow internet providers to withdraw payments 

### Requirements

- [ ] Receive payments from any address
- [ ] Check if an address can redeem a token
- [ ] Redeem a token

### Implementation Suggestions

- [ ] Maintain map of token id to address that token provides internet for
- [ ] Reference the ERC721 Contract that manages tokens
- [ ] etc... (more is welcome)
